definition.value: A phase of the estrous cycle that precedes estrus. During proestrus, the Graafian follicles undergo maturation.
The period in the estrous cycle associated with maximum sexual receptivity and fertility in non-primate female mammals.
The period following estrus during which the phenomena of estrus subside in those animals in which pregnancy or pseudopregnancy does not occur.
A reproductive behavior in which a parent cares for and rears offspring.
The regulated release of a hormone into the circulatory system.
The specific neuromuscular movement of a single organism in response to external or internal stimuli.

A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry. This process occurs in the uterus. Force generation involves a chemo-mechanical energy conversion step that is carried out by the actin/myosin complex activity, which generates force through ATP hydrolysis. The uterus is a muscular organ of the female mammal for containing and usually for nourishing the young during development prior to birth.
The behavior in which an organism produces sounds by a mechanism involving its respiratory system.
Any process involved in the controlled movement of a sperm cell.
A sex chromosome that has been inactivated.
A sex chromosome that has not been inactivated.
A day that is an exact number of years (to the day) since a given significant event occurred. Often preceded by an ordinal number indicating the number of years.
A day dedicated to bringing awareness to a certain cause and/or condition.
A day which is dedicated in memory of someone or something.
The anniversary of the day on which someone is born.
A day dedicated to bringing awareness to a certain civil cause and/or condition.
A day declared free from work by the state or government.

A marriage between partners of differing sexual orientations. The people involved in such a marriage may not be romantically or sexually compatible, for example if the marriage is between a heterosexual man and a homosexual woman. The term also applies when one of the partners involved is asexual and/or aromantic, leading to a mixed desire for sexual activity and/or romantic activity.
A broad genre encompassing fiction with certain elements that do not exist in the real world, often in the context of supernatural, futuristic or other imaginative themes.
Suicides organized by the particular method utilized.
The act of committing suicide where the method is hanging.
Surgical removal or artificial destruction of gonads accomplished by oneself.
A month which is dedicated in memory of someone or something.
A week dedicated to bringing awareness to a certain cause and/or condition.
A week dedicated to bringing awareness to a certain civil cause and/or condition.
A week dedicated to bringing awareness to a certain health-related cause and/or condition.
A transgender person who has HIV.
A cisgender person who has HIV.
Any intervention which utilizes androgens.
Any intervention which utilizes estrogens.
A child who is gender nonconforming.
Any process involving the economy, economics, or finances.
A recurrent and patterned process that involves the interactions or responses of individuals to one another which have attained stability.
Any series of calculations performed by mathematical methods.
A child who is transgender or otherwise gender nonconforming.
A transgender woman who has HIV.
An article which is an academic work and is published, or will be published, in an academic or scholarly journal.
An academic or scholarly journal is a periodical publication in which scholarship relating to a particular academic discipline is published.
A transgender man who has HIV.
One who advocates for social justice.
Suicides as they occur among adult transgender people.
The anniversary of the day on which someone died.
The anniversary of the day on which someone was married.
The sequence of events involved in the process of gametogenesis.
Any of various reproductive strategies utilized by animals.
The development of the embryo inside the body of the parent, eventually leading to live birth.

Mode of reproduction in which the zygotes develop in the female's oviducts, but find their nutrients from other tissues, whether skin or glandular tissue, oophagy, or adelphophagy (intra-uterine cannibalism in some sharks or in the black salamander Salamandra atra).

Mode of reproduction in which nutrients are provided by the female, often through a placenta, as in mammals (except for marsupials and monotremes). In the frog, Gastrotheca ovifera, embryos are fed by the mother through specialized gills. The lizard Pseudomoia pagenstecheri and most mammals use this form of viviparity.

Mode of reproduction in which fertilization is external, with the oocytes being released into the environment and fertilized outside the female's body by the male. This is common in molluscs, arthropods, and fishes, and is found in most frogs.
Suicides as they occur among young transgender people.
